","text":"SKARMORY is entirely encased in hard, protective armor. This POK\u00e9MON flies at close to 190 mph. It slashes foes with its wings that possess swordlike cutting edges."},{"version":"sapphire","text":"SKARMORY\u2019s steel wings become tattered and bashed in from repeated battles. Once a year, the battered wings grow back completely, restoring the cutting edges to their pristine state."},{"version":"emerald","text":"A POK\u00e9MON that has a body and wings of steel. People in the past used feathers fallen from SKARMORY to make swords and knives."},{"version":"firered","text":"After nesting in bramble bushes, the wings of its chicks grow hard from scratches by thorns."},{"version":"leafgreen","text":"Its sturdy wings look heavy, but its bones are hollow and light, allowing it to fly freely in the sky."},{"version":"diamond","text":"Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speeds over 180 mph."},{"version":"pearl","text":"Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speeds over 180 mph."},{"version":"platinum","text":"Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speeds over 180 mph."},{"version":"heartgold","text":"Its sturdy wings look heavy, but they are actually hollow and light, allowing it to fly freely in the sky."},{"version":"soulsilver","text":"After nesting in bramble bushes, the wings of its chicks grow hard from scratches by thorns."},{"version":"black","text":"Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speeds over 180 mph."},{"version":"white","text":"Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speeds over 180 mph."},{"version":"black-2","text":"Its heavy-looking iron body is actually thin and light, so it can fly at speeds over 180 mph."},{"version":"white-2","text":"Its heavy-looking iron body is actually thin and light, so it can fly at speeds over 180 mph."},{"version":"x","text":"After nesting in bramble bushes, the wings of its chicks grow hard from scratches by thorns."},{"version":"y","text":"Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speeds over 180 mph."},{"version":"omega-ruby","text":"Skarmory is entirely encased in hard, protective armor. This Pok\u00e9mon flies at close to 190 mph. It slashes foes with its wings that possess swordlike cutting edges."},{"version":"alpha-sapphire","text":"Skarmory\u2019s steel wings become tattered and bashed in from repeated battles. Once a year, the battered wings grow back completely, restoring the cutting edges to their pristine state."},{"version":"sun","text":"Its feathers, which fall off as it grows, are thin and sharp. In times long past, warriors used them as swords."},{"version":"moon","text":"Its metal body is sturdy, but it does rust rather easily. So on rainy days, this Pok\u00e9mon prefers to stay put in its nest."},{"version":"ultra-sun","text":"The wing feathers it sheds can be processed and made into knives whose sharpness is recognized by the finest chefs."},{"version":"ultra-moon","text":"Its body is draped in steel armor. It looks heavy, but it can fly at speeds of up to 185 miles an hour!"},{"version":"sword","text":"The pointed feathers of these Pok\u00e9mon are sharper than swords. Skarmory and Corviknight fight viciously over territory."},{"version":"shield","text":"People fashion swords from Skarmory\u2019s shed feathers, so this Pok\u00e9mon is a popular element in heraldic designs."}],"evo":{"name":"skarmory","level":0,"min_level":null,"trigger":null,"item":null,"held_item":null,"known_move":null,"known_move_type":null,"location":null,"min_affection":null,"min_beauty":null,"min_happiness":null,"needs_overworld_rain":false,"time_of_day":null,"turn_upside_down":false,"evolves_to":[]},"sprite":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/227.png","shiny":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/shiny/227.png","capture":25,"happiness":70,"growth":"slow","gender":4,"hatch":25,"ev"